						<summary>

						<p>On two faces of a mutilated pillar set up near the entrance into the fort in the village.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1539 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1461, Vikārin, [Bhadrapada] śu. 3,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1539 A.D., August 16, (Saturday).</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is very much damaged. Seems to refer to some gift made to god Varasiddhi Vināyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
